{"talk":{"id":5458,"name":"Natsai Audrey Chieza: Fashion has a pollution problem -- can biology fix it?","description":"Natsai Audrey Chieza is a designer on a mission -- to reduce pollution in the fashion industry while creating amazing new things to wear. In her lab, she noticed that the bacteria Streptomyces coelicolor makes a striking red-purple pigment, and now she's using it to develop bold, color-fast fabric dye that cuts down on water waste and chemical runoff, compared with traditional dyes. And she isn't alone in using synthetic biology to redefine our material future; think -- \"leather\" made from mushrooms and superstrong yarn made from spider-silk protein. We're not going to build the future with fossil fuels, Chieza says. We're going to build it with biology.","slug":"natsai_audrey_chieza_fashion_has_a_pollution_problem_can_biology_fix_it","recorded_at":"2017-10-04 00:00:00","published_at":"2017-11-29 16:01:33","updated_at":"2021-04-09 19:33:16","viewed_count":1166760,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":469,"name":"TED@BCG Milan"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a21c5426be585571ecd524c22ede9d08023a7179_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a21c5426be585571ecd524c22ede9d08023a7179_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a21c5426be585571ecd524c22ede9d08023a7179_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a21c5426be585571ecd524c22ede9d08023a7179_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/1af84b46c3b0b845018a4b86869d02a841a8cf62_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/NatsaiAudreyChieza_2017S-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":6562356,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/NatsaiAudreyChieza_2017S-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74